## -*- dok: swpatcitri; lang: en; coding: iso-8859-1; mode: fundamental; -*-
## title: History of the Limits of Patentability
->
[ [:SwpatcninoEn: Patent News]
]
----

How the patent system expanded and how theories of its limits emerged and were codified.

== More Dates ==

 * 1994-95 [http://www.uspto.gov/web/offices/com/doc/ipnii/ USPTO Paper: Intellectual Property and the National Information Infrastructure -- The Report of the Working Group on Intellectual Property Rights]
 * 1997-07-00 Commission launches Greenpaper on Community Patent and Software Patents
 * 1997-10-07 [:Monti9710En: EU Commissioner Monti: We need a directive "to protect computer software by patents"] 
----
 * 2002-03? !McCarthy, Wuermeling, Plooj, Rocard etc nominated rapporteurs
 * 2002-05? Economic and Social Council vote against software patents and EPO practise 
 * 2002-06 first !McCarthy paper (pro swpat, discrediting critics)
 * 2002-06 Bakels & Hugenholtz study (critical of swpat, demands completely new approach)
 * 2002-09 [http://swpat.ffii.org/papers/eubsa-swpat0202/prop/ FFII counter proposal]
 * 2002-11-07 JURI hearing, 
 * 2002-11 Danish Council presidency publishes [http://swpat.ffii.org/papers/eubsa-swpat0202/dkpto0209/ working party position in favor of unlimited patentability]
 * 2003-01 CULT vote against swpat, for freedom of publication and interoperation
 * 2003-02 ITRE vote for freedom of publication and interoperation
 * 2003-03 !McCarthy report to JURI
 * 2003-05-17 FFII conference on swpat in Brussels
 * 2003-06-17 JURI vote for fake limits on patentability
 * 2003-08-27 FFII demo in Brussels
 * 2003-09-23: plenary debate in EP after 129 amendments have been tabled, Bolkesteins threat
 * 2003-09-24: EP vote clearly restates nonpatentability of software, confines patent system to truly industrial products and processes (automated production of material goods), rejects program claims, and safeguards interoperability.
 * 2004-11: [http://swpat.ffii.org/papers/europarl0309/cec0311/ Comission DGIM pushing Council against Parliament]
 * 2004-01-29: [http://swpat.ffii.org/news/04/cons0129 Irish presidency's proposal for the council's position], reverts all amendments that limit patentability or enforcement, and re-introduces program claims.  The most extreme version ever.
 * 2004-03-17: latest version of [http://swpat.ffii.org/papers/europarl0309/cons0401 working group proposal], soon thereafter moved to !CoRePer
 * 2004-04-14 [http://swpat.ffii.org/news/04/cons0408/ FFII demo and conference on swpat in Brussels, amidst Council Presidency moves, Nokia campaign and MEP statements]
 * 2004-05-18 The Council of the European Union [http://swpat.ffii.org/papers/europarl0309/cons0401/ reaches a political agreement on common position] It is [http://swpat.ffii.org/xatra/cons0406/repr/ questionable wether a real qualified majority was reached]
 * 2005-02-02 The JURI Committee of the European Parliament [http://wiki.ffii.org/Restart050202En votes to restart the procedure for the directive "on the patentability of computer implemented inventions"]
 * 2005-02-28 The European Commission [http://wiki.ffii.org/Com050228En refuses to restart the procedure for the directive "on the patentability of computer implemented inventions"]
 * 2005-03-07 The Council of the European Union [http://www.nosoftwarepatents.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=439 reaches a common possition] after being postponed several times. Again it is [http://wiki.ffii.org/LtrFfiiCons050308En questionable wether a real qualified majority was reached and wether the procedures were followed correctly].
 * 2005-06-20 The JURI Committee of the European Parliament [http://wiki.ffii.org/Juri050620En adopts only few changes the Council's "common position"]
 * 2005-07-06 The European Parliament [http://wiki.ffii.org/Ep050706En rejects the directive "on the patentability of computer implemented inventions"]
